frameDefinitions: A recordable sequence of events is associated with a given Topic.
This frame concerns transparent nouns that denote Instances of Types of entities or events.
This scenario describes a series of Events, associated with a single Participant, i.e., the history of the Participant.
This frame contains words describing physical experiences that can affect virtually any part of the body.
A Fugitive avoids recapture by or on the authority of Authorities in relation to a Crime which the Fugitive has committed or is suspected of having committed.
This frame contains words for Individuals as viewed in terms of their participation in artistic performances.
frameExamples: And that is where the <t>history</t> of art begins.

The survey confirmed that management interference in team operations had increased , and <t><fex name='Instance'>instances</fex></t> of management decisions being taken without team consultation had also increased .
We've been worried about our recent hire's <t><fex name='Events'>history</fex></t> of deceiving employers.
He is in fact a <t>fugitive</t> of the law and you must inform the police if you see him.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject about which the history is given.
When the events concerning the <fen>Topic</fen> occured.
A thing or episode of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of thing or event of which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.

The <fen>Participant</fen> is either an active participant in all of the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Agent or Patient), or is more peripherally associated with the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Location or Topic).
The <fen>Events</fen> which the <fen>Participant</fen> is a part of. This role is used to mark the frame-evoking element.

The Experiencer is the being who has a physical experience on some part of his  or her body, or internally. Often information about this frame element is incorporated as a possessive determiner into the constituent expressing the Body Part, in which case it is not tagged separately (from Body Part), as shown below: My legs <t>hurt</t>! Sometimes, however, this frame element is expressed as an External Argument in its own right:  <fex name='Experiencer'>I</fex> <t>hurt</t> all over! Here, the phrase <ment>all over</ment> can be considered a kind of generalized Body Part expression, and the pronoun <ment>I</ment> expresses the Experiencer independently. With nouns and adjectives in this frame, the separate expression of the Experiencer is more common: <fex name='Experiencer'>I</fex> have a <t>pain</t> in my leg.

This role is the location on the body where the physical experience takes place, typically expressed as External Argument, often as PP complement: <fex name='Body_part'>My legs</fex> are a little <t>sore</t>. I'm a little <t>sore</t> <fex name='Body_part'>in my legs</fex>.
The <fen>Fugitive</fen> has escaped and/or is evading capture by law enforcement <fen>Authorities</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fugitive</fen> is evading law enforcement.
This role identifies the general <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Fugitive</fen> is located.
listRoleExamples: The role of the Byzantine Empire in <fex>European</fex> history is not understood by all.
I collected two <t>specimens</t> <fex>of this rare species</fex>.
We've been worried about <fex>our recent hire's</fex> history of deceiving employers.
We will focus on events in her recent <fex>history</fex>.
Only two years earlier <fex>she</fex> had been on the lam from charges of embezzlement.
He was a fugitive <fex>in the early 1990s</fex>.
Sloan, on the lam <fex>in Michigan</fex> for the last five months, is due to appear in court this Monday.
